name: AVAsyncProperty.Status
desc: Loaded status values for asynchronous properties.

items.name: case notYetLoaded
items.desc: The system hasn’t loaded a property value.

items.name: case loading
items.desc: The system is loading the property.

items.name: case loaded(Value)
items.desc: A property value is ready to use.

items.name: case failed(NSError)
items.desc: A property value fails to load.

items.name: static func == (AVAsyncProperty<Root, Value>.Status, AVAsyncProperty<Root, Value>.Status) -> Bool
items.desc: Returns a Boolean value that determines whether two statuses are equal.

items.name: static func != (AVAsyncProperty<Root, Value>.Status, AVAsyncProperty<Root, Value>.Status) -> Bool
items.desc: Returns a Boolean value that determines whether two statuses aren’t equal.
